  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Interview with Agnes Vertes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maiden name Katz.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Today is January 31, 1996.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My name is Michelle [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Landerberger. ?] We're conducting this interview in Weston, Connecticut, and the interview language is English.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was telling you about my first encounter with the treatment of the Jews by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it had a tremendous impact on me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This has been haunting me in my dreams and all through my lifetime.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't know if it's appropriate to mention, but when I saw and they're herding the people through the streets of Krakow, I was hysterical in the movie theater.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was absolutely hysterical.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My daughter, whom I took there, she didn't shed a tear, but I-- the whole thing came back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after that, we went to my mother's hiding place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father came there too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He risked coming out of his hiding place and he came to see us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No sooner did we all arrive there, there was an air raid.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, my mother thought we shouldn't go down to the shelter because we all had our story and my mother's story was that her husband had left for the front and, well, did not abandon her, but she had no way of supporting her two kids and therefore we were given to somebody else.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our story was coinciding with it, but not quite.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our story was that our father, Andrew Kovacs, was fighting the German side on the front and we had to be placed because our mother is a refugee from Transylvania.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because by that time the Russian's were encroaching on Transylvania, and so a lot of Hungarian-speaking people came back to Hungary from Transylvania.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, the sirens started, and to me, that gave me the chills, the sirens.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They still do.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
